data.title: Try Ceviche... Good visit!!!
data.text:
Go there and try ceviche :-)
Place is clean, have a good service I prices. If you like Mexican cuisine I highly recommend to go there.

data.title: Nice night out
data.text: Good outside seating, good drink selection, we liked the menu but only can do so much with Mexican dishes.  Better than any chain.  Support local restaurants.

data.title: Overpriced, weak margaritas
data.text:
Place is located in trendy part of Carmel.  Service was friendly and good.  Chips and salsa were good.  I like frozen margaritas and the only ones they have ready made are the flavored margaritas, not traditional lime.  I got the frozen strawberry.  Medium size.  It was $11.  It tasted like a very sweet slurpee, like candy.  I could taste no alcohol.  I drank it and did not feel a thing.  I should have said something but I was hoping the tequila would eventually kick in but nothing.  I order the same size frozen house margarita at my usual Mexican joint and am usually feeling it after drinking about 1/3 of it.  My wife got a skinny margarita.  It was watered down and tasteless. We only got an appetizer after being turned off by the margaritas. 

I guess b/c of their location they think they can charge high prices for lame drinks.

data.title: Poor customer service and lies
data.text:
The service here was abysmal.  We were seated quickly and the food came out fairly quickly, but my order was wrong.  I had asked for steak in my chimichanga, which was one of the choices, but it came out with chicken.  Our waitress never came back to check and after waiting 10 minutes trying to get someone's attention, I finally saw the hostess and asked her to get our waitress.  Another 5 minutes passed and our waitress finally showed up.  When I told her the problem, she simply took the plate and walked away, no apology or even acknowledgement.  

Generally when something is prepared incorrectly, a restaurant will quickly remake the dish, but not in this case.  My husband finished his entire meal before my corrected meal came out and my corrected meal did not come out hot.  When I asked to speak to a manager, it took another 10 minutes and finally a waitress came out and said there is nothing they can do for us.  Again, no apology.  The hostess saw we were having trouble and she did apologize but there was nothing she could do, obviously.  She did tell us that there was no manager on duty for that shift and that the owner was not there.  So it seems that they were trying to lead us to believe that the waitress we spoke to was a manager when, in fact, there was no manager there.

This is the first time I have ever had to leave a restaurant without being able to eat.  While my husband did get to eat, his burrito was extra thin and only had meat on the ends.  The center of the burrito was empty.  I will never return and I wouldn't recommend anyone else go either.

data.title: Good food but 2014 salmonella outbreak have marked this off our list.
data.text: Unfortunately this beautiful restaurant had a critical salmonella issue in 2014. We have eaten at Agave several times prior to the 2014 incidents but are no longer comfortable dining there. In 2014, seven people were hospitalized and the health department cited the restaurant with 19 critical and 21 non-critical violations. Enjoy at your own risk.

data.title: I eat here every time I'm in Carmel!
data.text:
This a great restaurant in the arts district of Carmel!  The margaritas and the food are tasty! 

The service is always great, particularly in the early part of the evening.

data.title: Good quality Mexican cuisine
data.text: We've been here several times.  This is good quality food with good service.  The drinks are above-average.  The setting is good.

data.title: Dinner with ladies
data.text: I ate here with a group of ladies and the food was good. I had a chimichanga (shrimp) and it was fabulous!

data.title: Nice surprise!
data.text: I've driven by the Agave Bar & Grill several times but have never gone in until now.  Little did I know what I'd been missing.  Such a cute, quaint place.  Their food and drink menu was large.  I had the Agave chimichunga and it was fantastic (and so was my margarita)!  The service we received was very good also.  This will definitely be a regular stop on my travels through Carmel.

data.title: Well worth it.
data.text: Every time I have eaten at Agave I have experienced very good food and service.  The fajitas are my favorite, and the salsa is excellent.

data.title: Nice upscale Mexican food
data.text: Ate lunch there today. The decor was sleek and modern. The food was great. Price was reasonable. Service was great. We were visiting from out of town and will return.

data.title: Great lunch with kid friendly options
data.text: We enjoyed this place very much for lunch as the food was delicious and our waitress was friendly and attentive. Kids menu was a few items-but staples-chicken strips, mac& cheese if your children won't eat Mexican. We'll definitely go back!

data.title: Delicious!
data.text: We have been here several times. Every time the service is great and the food has been delicious. Don't forget a pitcher of the regular margaritas.

data.title: Eat Local Mexican, Not at the Chains
data.text: This is a very good option for locally owned Mexican in Carmel. I eat here frequently with my family for dinner but went to lunch recently with a friend at Agave. Service is quick and friendly, food is very well prepared and it is reasonably priced. $20 for lunch for two of us and we both left full. Dinner prices are more expensive but why eat at one of the crummy chains when you can support a local business.

data.title: Excellent food and drink
data.text: Love, love, love this restaurant- it serves authentic Mexican food and a great margarita!  When the weather is nice, you can be seated on the outdoor patio.  The service is a little slow, but is always friendly.

data.title: great new venue
data.text: I understand this is one of the newest restaurants in town.  I was going to be in town for a convention tour and researched eateries close to our destination.  The online menu showed  Hawaii Chicken which sounded very good.  I was not disapointed.  It was very good and reasonably priced.  Other meals served at nearby tables looked very good and attractively served.  I would go there again if I am back in town.

data.title: Bandera Burrito FTW
data.text:
I love this little Mexican restaurant. It's nice to sit outside on a nice day, but the decor inside the establishment is nice as well. Especially when they have the upstairs open and you can check out the murals and glass sculpture upstairs.

My favorite burrito started out as a special but has since been added to the regular menu. It is called the Bandera Burrito. It literally has everything in it. Chicken, steak, shrimp and churrizo, veggies and topped with 3 difference sauces (red, green and white which makes the mexican flag on top of the burrito which is lovely presentation too)

So good! Unfortunately since this burrito arrived I have not eaten anything else, so I can't speak to much else on the menu, but I'm sure other stuff is good as well. Haha

data.title: Fantastic local Mexican
data.text: Great food, great atmosphere and even better margaritas. This upscale Mexican restaurant is great for a date night.

data.title: Beyond the Typical!
data.text: A great menu with specialty dishes that you don't get at the average Mexican restaurant.  Quail fajitas, Tilapia, and other nontraditional dishes. Each dish we ordered was fantastic.  The house salsa was also fresh and delicious.  The building is somewhat small, but beautifully decorated and has two floors for dining.  No actual bar to sit at, but a full service bar for ordering.  The house margarita was great...and comes in pitchers for groups.  Outside seating is available if the weather permits.

data.title: Delicious food, atmosphere, and margaritas
data.text: Although I gravitate toward regular Tex-Mex, Agave also offers more upscale fare--particularly seafood--that others might prefer. I'm not a seafood lover, so can't offer any recommendations. However, I am a fan of everything I've tried here: chimichangas, tacos, tostadas, guacamole, chips and salsa, and the Agave margarita. The food is first-rate, and the service is courteous and attentive.
